The paper proposes a novel approach to multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) that utilizes deep learning techniques such as self-attention mechanism and message-generation technique inspired by the NerveNet architecture. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories as they are related to artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also focuses on multi-agent domains, which suggests that cs.MA is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper uses a relevance graph representation of the environment, which is related to natural language processing and graph theory, indicating that cs.CL is a possible category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to the Pommerman game, which involves visual perception and decision-making, suggesting that cs.CV is also a possible category.
